<div id="review_518674411" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/518674411" />
    <a title="MJ Nicholls" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2386804-mj-nicholls"><img alt="MJ Nicholls" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1374341850p2/2386804.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/518674411?book_show_action=true">Jan 27, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="MJ Nicholls" class="user" itemprop="url" name="MJ Nicholls" href="/user/show/2386804-mj-nicholls">MJ Nicholls</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2386804-mj-nicholls?shelf=latin-american">latin-american</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2386804-mj-nicholls?shelf=novellas">novellas</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2386804-mj-nicholls?shelf=art-or-illustrated">art-or-illustrated</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2386804-mj-nicholls?shelf=nyrb">nyrb</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer518674411" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17678965541959921283">Lacking in the satirical surrealism found in his later (and some say lesser) NYRB book <i>Asleep in the Sun</i>, unfortunately this one failed to sustain my attention despite forty pages of anticipatory eagerness. The narrator, nameless, mooches around an island spying on a gypsy woman and is evicted from her presence by bearded Frenchmen. Naturally, she is beautiful, naturally he falls in love with her, then something happens to do with photographs and people dying and I didn’t understand most of it, </span>
  <span id="freeText17678965541959921283" style="display:none">Lacking in the satirical surrealism found in his later (and some say lesser) NYRB book <i>Asleep in the Sun</i>, unfortunately this one failed to sustain my attention despite forty pages of anticipatory eagerness. The narrator, nameless, mooches around an island spying on a gypsy woman and is evicted from her presence by bearded Frenchmen. Naturally, she is beautiful, naturally he falls in love with her, then something happens to do with photographs and people dying and I didn’t understand most of it, due to the absence of an interesting character or situation or compelling narrative style, and too much technical-contraption-waffle of the kind found in the most boring nouveau roman stuff.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17678965541959921283" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


